On 15 Nov, 2010, at 19:19 , coderman wrote:

>
> the cuda cards are killing bitcoin, why bother?
>
>   (i suppose it is an interesting footnote...)



Nothing could be further from the truth.  Mining/Minting operations have
little/nothing to do with the viability of the network itself.  It's a novel
way of dealing with inflation, but, if anything, the easy availability of
cheap and fast GPUs is accelerating adoption.

Opportunists will quickly drive the profit from generating down to almost
exactly that of the power costs, but that's to be expected.  They are also the
driving force behind a free market.  Or do you think they are killing those,
too? :)

- -jp

